---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Methodology — AI PM Workbench" description="The thinking framework behind the AI PM Workbench" isEn={true}>
  <main class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-3">Methodology</h1>
    <p class="text-muted-foreground mb-10 max-w-2xl">How the Workbench structures AI product thinking — from problem framing to delivery artifacts.</p>

    <div class="space-y-8">
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">Core Principle</h2>
        <p class="text-muted-foreground">Most AI product failures come from starting with the technology rather than the problem. The Workbench enforces a structured progression: define the problem and user first, then choose the AI capability, then set evaluation criteria, and only then generate delivery artifacts.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">The 4-Step Workflow</h2>
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <div class="bg-card rounded-xl ring-1 ring-foreground/10 p-5">
            <h3 class="font-medium mb-1">1. Product Framing</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground">Define the business scenario, target users, current workflow, and knowledge context. This step prevents building AI for problems that don't exist.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-card rounded-xl ring-1 ring-foreground/10 p-5">
            <h3 class="font-medium mb-1">2. Design Intelligence</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground">Choose the right AI capability (classification, generation, RAG, agent) and design the workflow boundary. This step answers: does this need an agent, or is a simpler approach sufficient?</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-card rounded-xl ring-1 ring-foreground/10 p-5">
            <h3 class="font-medium mb-1">3. Evaluate and Risk</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground">Set evaluation metrics, acceptance criteria, and identify production risks. Suggestion chips help you cover metrics you might miss.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-card rounded-xl ring-1 ring-foreground/10 p-5">
            <h3 class="font-medium mb-1">4. Export</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground">Generate 6 structured documents: product brief, workflow spec, evaluation plan, acceptance criteria, coding agent handoff, and CLAUDE.md starter. Copy, download, or continue with AI.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">Key Concepts</h2>
        <div class="grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-2">
          <div class="bg-card rounded-xl ring-1 ring-foreground/10 p-5">
            <h3 class="font-medium mb-1">Vibe Coding</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground">Using coding agents to turn product intent into prototypes. PM focuses on architecture and evaluation, not implementation details.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-card rounded-xl ring-1 ring-foreground/10 p-5">
            <h3 class="font-medium mb-1">Harness Engineering</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground">Designing context, tools, constraints, checks, and feedback systems for coding agents — not writing code yourself.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-card rounded-xl ring-1 ring-foreground/10 p-5">
            <h3 class="font-medium mb-1">Agent vs. Non-Agent</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground">Not every AI product needs an agent. The Workbench helps you decide: multi-step reasoning and tool use justify agents; deterministic rules and simple retrieval do not.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-card rounded-xl ring-1 ring-foreground/10 p-5">
            <h3 class="font-medium mb-1">Privacy-First</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground">All data stays in your browser. No servers, no API calls, no accounts. Your product ideas never leave your machine.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">Resources</h2>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-muted-foreground">
          <li><a href="/AI-PM-Operating-Playbook/en/ai-pm-role/" class="text-emerald-400 hover:text-emerald-300 transition-colors">AI PM Role &rarr;</a> — What it means to be an AI PM</li>
          <li><a href="/AI-PM-Operating-Playbook/en/vibe-coding/" class="text-emerald-400 hover:text-emerald-300 transition-colors">Vibe Coding &rarr;</a> — PM + coding agent collaboration</li>
          <li><a href="/AI-PM-Operating-Playbook/en/harness-engineering/" class="text-emerald-400 hover:text-emerald-300 transition-colors">Harness Engineering &rarr;</a> — Directing AI to write code</li>
          <li><a href="/AI-PM-Operating-Playbook/en/prompt-to-ontology/" class="text-emerald-400 hover:text-emerald-300 transition-colors">Prompt-to-Ontology Case Study &rarr;</a> — Real project example</li>
        </ul>
      </section>
    </div>
  </main>
</Layout>
